Title: Air Jordan 1 Mid True Blue
Body (HTML):
The highly popular Air Jordan 1 Mid awaits you at Costyled in a True Blue colorway that you need to discover right away.

Originally designed in the early 2000s for the Asian market, particularly Japan, this mid-top version of Peter Moore's classic reveals itself in a color palette that is both understated, refreshing, and ultra-trendy.

As its name suggests, the Jordan 1 Mid True Blue showcases blue hues, specifically on its inner lining, the iconic Nike logo on each side panel, as well as the laces and outsole.

This famous True Blue, which gave the pair its name, enhances the design of the leather upper with a white base combined with gray overlay reinforcements.

The Jordan Wings on the upper exterior panels stand out in a white accent, just like the midsole.

Although conceived with a 100% lifestyle purpose in mind, the Air Jordan 1 Mid has retained the technical features of the original high-top version, starting with the perforations necessary for foot breathability on the toe box and, of course, the Nike Air cushioning technology, which is appropriately present at the heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid True is, in fact, as comfortable as it is stylish.

Looking for another colorway? Discover the Air Jordan 1 Mid Grey Sail at Costyled!

Practical advice: This model fits true to size, and we recommend you take your usual size.

Designed in the early 2000s for the Asian market, especially Japan, this mid-top iteration of Peter Moore's timeless classic unveils itself in a color palette that's simultaneously understated, refreshing, and ultra-fashionable.

True to its name, the Jordan 1 Mid True Blue features blue accents, specifically on its inner lining, the famous Nike logo on each side panel, as well as the laces and outsole.

The Jordan Wings on the upper exterior panels stand out with a white contrast, just like the midsole.

Though envisioned with a 100% lifestyle focus, the Air Jordan 1 Mid has retained the technical features of the original high-top version, starting with the perforations necessary for foot breathability on the toe box and, naturally, the Nike Air cushioning technology, which is properly implemented at the heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid True is indeed both comfortable and trendy.
